Submission from: xia.elen.utah.edu (155.99.23.200)
Submitted by: peskin


A simple infinite loop specified in VHDL as 
	loop
		...
	end loop
Should be equivalent to 
	while ( <always true expression> ) loop
		...
	end loop
However, consider the following:

481 xia:examples/vhd> diff {winery8,loop}.vhd
21d20
<     variable one : integer := 1;
28c27
<   while ( one = one ) loop
---
>   loop
482 xia:examples/vhd> atacs -lv patron3.vhd winery8.vhd wine_shop.vhd
